f=Cybersecurity/bastion/custom/network-security/SKILL.md · in=design maintenance network security controls segmentation, firewall/security group policy, zero-trust network access (ZTNA), network monitoring limit blast radius prevent lateral movement. bastion designs network security architecture detects gaps; operator/ops implements changes (the security-inversion). · p=flat network enemy security: any system reach any system, single compromised host becomes full network compromise. Network security creates boundaries segments, firewalls, micro-perimeters breach one zone doesn't become breach everywhere. · wu=Designing reviewing network architecture new system service., "Segment network," "firewall rule review," "is our network secure.", Network security review cadence., After breach/incident involved lateral movement (lessons rule changes). · st:/ Protocol=`NETWORK INVENTORY (segments, subnets, traffic flows, trust zones) \· → SEGMENTATION REVIEW (are boundaries between trust zones enforced?) \· → FIREWALL/SG AUDIT (rules: least-privilege, unused, over-permissive) \· → ZTNA CHECK (is there implicit trust? can internal traffic move laterally unchecked?) \· → MONITORING REVIEW (are network anomalies detected? → feeds cortex)` · in=**Map trust zones.** Identify segments data sensitivity (per veil's classification) function (public-facing, internal-service, data-store, admin, developer, corporate). network least: public application data tier, boundaries between them. **Review segmentation.** compromised web server reach database directly? developer laptop reach production? yes, segmentation insufficient recommend network ACLs, security groups, separate VPCs. **Audit firewall/security group rules.** Least-privilege: rule allowing 0.0.0.0/0 (any IP) any port finding. Rules without documented business owner purpose candidates removal. Rules hits 90+ days candidates removal. **Zero-trust network access.** implicit trust based network location. connection authenticated authorized. Internal traffic assumed safe micro-segmentation per-request auth feasible. **Monitor.** Network anomalies (unexpected outbound connections, data exfiltration volumes, new protocols unusual ports) feed cortex's detection-engineering. you can't see traffic, you can't detect breach. **bastion specs; operator/ops applies.** inversion bastion designs audits; operator ops deploys firewall rules, configures network ACLs, implements segmentation changes. · of=`## Network Security Review: [scope] — [date] \· Trust zones: [list with data sensitivity per veil] \· Segmentation: [public→app: enforced / app→data: enforced / admin→prod: gated] \· Firewall/SG rules: [total \· over-permissive \· no-owner \· unused >90d] \· ZTNA: [implicit trust found \· micro-segmentation status]` · pr=**Segmentation foundational.** Flat networks indefensible; boundaries blast-radius limit., **Least-privilege rule.** Firewall rules specific source, destination, port, purpose any/any., **No implicit trust.** ZTNA: location grant access; connection authenticated., **Audit cadence.** Rules accumulate; stale rules attack surface., **If you can't see it, you can't detect it.** Network monitoring prerequisite cortex., **bastion specs; operator/ops applies.** inversion. · f=network diagram asset inventory start what's discoverable (cloud console, scans), labeled "provisional partial visibility." Flag incomplete inventory risk., Legacy flat network recommend segmentation time-boxed migration plan compensating controls (host-level firewalls, application-layer auth) interim., Unable enforce segmentation technically document gap, recommend compensating controls, route warden risk. · b:with Other Skills=**cloud-posture** (sibling): finds cloud SG/security group misconfigs (public buckets, open ports). skill designs network policy checks verify against., **hardening-baselines** (sibling): host-level firewall rules hardening baseline; network-level segmentation skill., **infra-vuln-management** (sibling): network segmentation contains blast radius unpatched systems two skills complementary., **cortex** (Cybersecurity): network monitoring feeds detection; breach involving lateral movement triggers network security lessons., **veil** (Cybersecurity): trust zones defined data sensitivity veil's classification., **ops (Engineering)**: implements network changes through deploy gate., **warden**: network gaps (flat segments, over-permissive rules, monitoring) register risks.